This is the moment a 'worse for wear' student was attacked by a 'hugger mugger' who squeezed his throat until he lost consciousness before stealing his  £5,000 Rolex.

The 24-year-old had been on a night out in central London when his attacker began talking to him about martial arts and acting out restraint moves.

As the student turned around, the attacker suddenly put his arm across his throat and squeezed, causing the victim’s legs to crumple as he passed out briefly and fell to the ground. 

