Detectives investigating the attack have today released CCTV footage of the incident, which happened near Regents Street, in an attempt to track down the suspect, who they described as a 'hugger mugger'.

'The suspect targeted his victim carefully, choosing someone who was a bit the worse for wear after a night out, alone and smartly dressed,' said Investigating officer Detective constable Michael Heaney.

'The method he uses is not something we have seen before in this area and is a concern.

'Had the suspect applied more pressure the victim could have been far more seriously injured.

